# IDP Management — Project Conventions

**Phase:** PoC. Optimize for simplicity and speed. Do not add packages, patterns, or abstractions not listed in .clinerules or spec-base.md. When in doubt, do less and ask for clarification.

## Naming Conventions

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Variables & functions | camelCase | `getUserData`, `isLoading` |
| React components | PascalCase | `UserProfile`, `NavigationBar` |
| Files & directories | kebab-case | `user-profile.tsx`, `api-route.ts` |
| TS interfaces/types | PascalCase | `UserResponse`, `DashboardProps` |
| Prisma models | PascalCase, camelCase fields | `User`, `IdpSubmission` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`, `SESSION_COOKIE_NAME` |
| Zod schemas | PascalCase + Schema | `IdpFormSchema` |

## TypeScript

- Strict mode. Never use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow the type.
- All Server Actions return `ActionResult<T>` from `@/types/index.ts`.
- Never throw from a Server Action — always return `{ success: false, error: string }`.
- Define shared types/Zod schemas in `@/types/index.ts` only.

## Component Structure

- Default to React Server Components. Add `use client` only when needed (browser APIs, event handlers, hooks).
- Keep `use client` at leaf nodes.
- Use Server Actions (`@/actions/`) for mutations. Never call Prisma from Client Components.
- Pass data from Server Components as props. No fetches inside Client Components unless required.
- Imports: absolute paths with `@/`. Order: React/Next.js → external libs → internal `@/` → styles.

## Data Fetching

- Fetch in Server Components with async/await.
- Server Actions for mutations. Call `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()` after success.
- Never call a Server Action inside `useEffect`.

## Session & Auth

- Never read/write cookies directly. Use `getSession()`, `setSession()`, `clearSession()` from `@/lib/session.ts`.
- Validate session at top of every Server Action before any DB operation.

## Error Handling

- Wrap Server Actions and Route Handlers in try/catch.
- Return `{ success: false, error: string }` — never expose raw errors.
- Use `app/error.tsx` for UI error boundary.
- Client: Error Boundaries. Log with `console.error` only in development.

## Database

- Use Prisma singleton from `@/lib/prisma.ts`.
- Validate input with Zod before Prisma operations.
- Never expose raw DB types — map to types in `@/types/index.ts`.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only. No inline styles, CSS Modules, or styled-components.
- Use shadcn/ui first. Customize via `className` only.

## Patterns

- Early returns; guard clauses at top of functions.
- Business logic in `@/lib/` or `@/actions/`; UI logic in `@/components/`.
- Server Actions: validate → call lib → return ActionResult. Keep them thin.

## Testing

- Out of scope for PoC. Do not generate test files.

